  "id": "Hackney-2024_0131",
  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-63cc87c6-7fff-29e5-4d2d-025b572b6449&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;In the absence of robust marketing evidence having been submitted in support of the development, the proposed change of use from office (Use Class E(g)) to a large HMO (Use Class Sui Generis) would result in the loss of office floorspace. The applicant has, therefore, failed to provide evidence to demonstrate a lack of demand for the existing office floorspace, contrary to the objectives of Policy LP27(Protecting and Promoting Office Floorspace in the Borough) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Policy E1(Offices) of the London Plan (2021).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-94fc6979-7fff-d2d1-8945-bddfd141c6d7&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;By reason of the scale and first-floor positioning of the proposed external communal amenity space, the impact of which would be exacerbated by the introduction of associated paraphernalia, the development would appear as an incongruous feature detrimental to the character, appearance and significance of the locally listed building and appearance of the wider townscape. The development would, therefore, conflict with Policies LP1(Design Quality and Local Character) and LP4 (Non Designated Heritage Assets) &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10.5pt; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Policies D4(Delivering good design) and HC1(Heritage conservation and growth) of the London Plan (2021).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-7ec9775f-7fff-2d60-0d70-b5aee24a1b4e&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;By reason of the close proximity of the communal external amenity space with neighbouring windows to the rear of 123 Stoke Newington Road, combined with the uncharacteristic provision of external amenity space at first floor level within the immediate area, the external communal amenity space would result in direct overlooking of these neighbouring windows and give rise to undue levels of noise and disturbance. As such, the development would fail to safeguard neighbouring amenity, contrary to Policy LP2(Development and Amenity) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-8fcd0d09-7fff-b9a8-9a0c-ef67e44f70b4&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10.5pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space-collapse: preserve;&quot;&gt;In the absence of a Section 106 legal Agreement (S106) to secure appropriate rent levels in accordance with the Local Housing Allowance, the development would conflict with Policy LP22 (Houses in Multiple Occupation (HMO)) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure car-free housing, would be likely to promote the use of non-sustainable modes of transport and contribute to air pollution and congestion in the surrounding area, contrary to policies T6 (Car Parking) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP45 (Parking and Car Free Development) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#x27;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
